35 per cent have tested positive for coronavirus antibodies, meaning they’ve had the disease at some point.Embakasi West had the highest number of people infected at 60 per cent.Age group 30-39 were the most affected, with 43 per cent of them infected. One in three people in Nairobi has been infected by Covid-19, according to a new analysis of blood samples. 

The analysis, done by the Kenya Medical Research Institute (Kemri), Washington State University Global Health- Kenya and the University of Nairobi, showed that the overall seroprevalence of Covid-19 in Nairobi stood at 35 per cent in the nine months since the first case was reported in Kenya. 



