For Kenya to know how many people were infected in the community and help plan for the right responses, an antibody test should help, however, it is not available in the country and Kenyans wishing to have the test may have to wait. Health ministry says the number of declared infections is now 100,422 whereas the death toll is 1,753. This comes on top of an earlier announcement by the AU that it had secured 270 million vaccine doses. The medical agency rejected an offer from Northlink GSC Ltd, which was ready to supply PPE at Sh4,500 instead of the Sh9,000. TI noted that the report revealed a direct link between persistent corruption and management of the Covid-19 pandemic.